m to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Rogier de Muschamp was born in 1020, in Normandy, France. He married F de Muschamp before 1040, in France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1062, in France, at the age of 42."},"et":{"1020–1062":"1020–1062","1024–Female":"1024–Surnud","1044–1120":"1044–1120","1024":"1024","1044":"1044","1120":"1120","1020":"1020","before 1040":"enne 1040","1062":"1062","Muschamp, Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1020–1062":"1020–1062","1024–Female":"1024–Kuollut","1044–1120":"1044–1120","1024":"1024","1044":"1044","1120":"1120","1020":"1020","before 1040":"ennen vuotta 1040","1062":"1062","Muschamp, Normandie, France":"Normandie, Ranska","France":"Ranska","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1020–1062":"1020–1062","1024–Female":"1024–Décédée","1044–1120":"1044–1120","1024":"1024","1044":"1044","1120":"1120","1020":"1020","before 1040":"avant 1040","1062":"1062","Muschamp, Normandie, France":"Normandie, France","France":"France","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Rogier de Muschamp est né en 1020, à Normandie, France. Il a épousé F de Muschamp avant 1040, à France. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1062, à France, à l’âge de 42 ans."},"de":{"1020–1062":"1020–1062","1024–Female":"1024–Verstorben","1044–1120":"1044–1